{"name": "ccorp-yaml-include-relative-path", "metadata": {"name": "ccorp-yaml-include-relative-path", "version": "0.0.4", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/marsoloGit/ccorp_yaml_include", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["ruamel.yaml"], "summary": "Exactly ccorp-yaml-include package with a bug fix and support of relative paths for included aliases", "upload_time": 1593580091}, "documentation": ["# CCorp Ruamel.YAML Include Extension\n\nThis package is exactly ccorp-yaml-include package(a fork of ccorp-yaml-include) that contains a bug fix (init of YAML didn't accept a 'typ' kwargs that was a list)\nIt also allows to use `!include` tag with a relative path for aliases, e.g.\ninstead of just writing: \n<br> *!include bear_common.yaml* <br>(which means that bear_common.yaml should be located in the same directory as your yaml file) \n\nyou can have:\n<br>*!include ../common_data/bear_common.yaml* <br>(which means that bear_common.yaml in now located in a separate folder 'common_data')\n- **version 0.0.4**: a bug related to ExcludingConstructor.construct_sequence() method to miss a parameter called 'deep', fixed.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ccorp.ruamel.yaml.include", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [{"name": "ccorp.ruamel.yaml.include.include_compositor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "anchor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccorp.ruamel.yaml.include.exclude_filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key_node", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value_node", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "ccorp.ruamel.yaml.include.yaml", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccorp.ruamel.yaml.include.